The paper deals with the problem of approximate pattern matching in a stream, which involves both data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also involves combinatorial problems, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another likely category. The use of encoding techniques and space-efficient algorithms suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category. The paper also involves optimization of space and time complexity, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible category. Finally, the use of probabilistic techniques and analysis of algorithms suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
